:133:"https://www.chegg.com/homework-help/questions-and-answers/following-chair-conformations-represented-haworth-projection-shown-q7690909";s:6:"domain";s:13:"www.chegg.com";}i:19;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:40:"chair conformation to haworth projection";s:4:"slug";s:40:"chair-conformation-to-haworth-projection";s:5:"title";s:66:"Solved The Fischer Projection The Haworth Projection And Chegg Com";s:3:"alt";s:5:"chegg";s:3:"url";s:96:"https://d2vlcm61l7u1fs.cloudfront.net/media%2F477%2F47746b12-37b2-43d4-abed-e18380add914%2Fimage";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTZsREYwVsnzkt62_XARmW_D-xKH-cIaiLMGEr0TlODH1d6YCohwuaLczR9--LCsxL-KF8";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:405;s:6:"height";i:700;s:6:"source";s:158:"https://www.chegg.com/homework-help/questions-and-answers/fischer-projection-haworth-projection-chair-conformation-d-galactose-shown--d-talosc-c2-ep-q12571353";s:6:"domain";s:13:"www.chegg.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:40:"chair conformation to haworth projection";s:4:"slug";s:40:"chair-conformation-to-haworth-projection";s:5:"title";s:91:"Converting Between Fischer Haworth And Chair Forms Of Carbohydrates Organic Chemistry Tutor";s:3:"alt";s:23:"organic chemistry tutor";s:3:"url";s:87:"https://www.organicchemistrytutor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Haworth-projection.png";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRMDnzIZVPDbFQyEoSMZUM_MtfJ8U-R92R9jg";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:362;s:6:"height";i:988;s:6:"source";s:112:"https://www.organicchemistrytutor.com/topic/converting-between-fischer-haworth-and-chair-forms-of-carbohydrates/";s:6:"domain";s:29:"www.organicchemistrytutor.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:43:{i:0;s:174:"This pretty much summarizes a clean and straightforward method of converting from Fischer projection to Haworth projection to chair conformation for your typical aldohexoses.";i:1;s:107:"Occasionally instructors will ask you to do the opposite and convert from the chair to Haworth and Fischer.";i:2;s:336:"Drawing a Sugars Chair Conformation from a Haworth Structure or Fischer Projection If you have either the Haworth structure or the Fischer projection of the sugar drawing the chair conformation of the sugar is easy as long as you remember the orientations of the axial and equatorial bonds on each carbon atom of the chair conformation.";i:3;s:69:"For example given the Haworth structure the chair conformation for D.";i:4;s:26:"Draw the Hs and OH groups.";i:5;s:109:"All the groups on the right side in the Fischer projection point down the groups on the left are pointing up.";i:6;s:54:"Convert the Haworth to a chair conformation if needed.";i:7;s:103:"The groups pointing up in a Haworth stay up in the chair and down stay down either axial or equatorial.";i:8;s:164:"HAWORTH PROJECTIONS AND CHAIR CONFORMATIONS A Haworth projection is a common way of illustrating cyclic structures with multiple substituents such as carbohydrates.";i:9;s:66:"They clearly outline the cis trans relation ships of substituents.";i:10;s:40:"F1 Shown below are two forms of glucose.";i:11;s:55:"Draw the most stable chair conformation for each 2 pts.";i:12;s:201:"Can you tell if the ring will be beta or alpha in the haworth projection chair conformation by just looking at the Fischer projection or must you be told first before creating the two from the Fischer.";i:13;s:32:"If so could someone explain how.";i:14;s:105:"Ive seen a bunch of websites and they all seem to say that you wont be able to tell from a Fischer alone.";i:15;s:232:"In this biochemistryorganic chemistry blog post we discuss the basic theory of carbohydrates emphasizing the various ways - Fischer projections Haworth projections chair conformations - that can be used to represent these molecules.";i:16;s:166:"F HAWORTH PROJECTIONS AND CHAIR CONFORMATIONS A Haworth projection is a common way of illustrating cyclic structures with multiple substituents such as carbohydrates.";i:17;s:66:"They clearly outline the cis trans relation ships of substituents.";i:18;s:84:"C 2 OH is on the right side of the Fischer and ends up on the bottom of the Haworth.";i:19;s:80:"C 3 OH is on the left side of the Fischer and ends up on the top of the Haworth.";i:20;s:84:"C 4 OH is on the right side of the Fischer and ends up on the bottom of the Haworth.";i:21;s:138:"Also when converting Haworth to Chair do we have to match the upward facing groups on the Haworth to upward facing positions on the chair.";i:22;s:68:"The Haworth has 2 upward methyl groups and 1 downward facing methyl.";i:23;s:202:"But in A the left equatorial one is facing upward as axial in that position is downward the middle axial methyl is upward and the right equatorial methyl is downward as axial in that position is upward.";i:24;s:30:"This doesnt match the Haworth.";i:25;s:39:"Their students today for this question.";i:26;s:97:"They want to draw a hard worth protection in a chair confirmation of peple al fatih man no pound.";i:27;s:22:"Renault side our musc.";i:28;s:163:"About Press Copyright Contact us Creators Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy Safety How YouTube works Test new features Press Copyright Contact us Creators.";i:29;s:42:"The orientation of the chair is important.";i:30;s:120:"The foot-rest of the chair is on the right hand side which is to say that the axial substituent on carbon 1 points down.";i:31;s:122:"To convert a chair form to a Haworth projection number the carbons 1 through 6 and then draw the Haworth template next to.";i:32;s:51:"Kuchen Backofen Alpha D Glucose Fischer Projektion.";i:33;s:128:"As can be seen both fischer and haworth projections are two standard ways of illustrating the stereochemistry of a carbohydrate.";i:34;s:178:"Whilst the haworth projection is more commonly used these days and a chair conformation can help to depict the atoms position in space the fischer projection certainly still has.";i:35;s:88:"Draw the Haworth projection for chair conformation of 